OL,3,CHealth board admits causing 'life-
OL,4,Cchanging' injuries to child during
OL,5,Cbirth
OL,7,FSwansea Bay University Health Board
OL,8,Fhas apologised to the parents of a
OL,9,Fseverely disabled child after
OL,10,Fadmitting being responsible for his
OL,11,Fbrain injuries, ITV Wales has learnt.
OL,13,F6-year-old Gethin Channon suffered
OL,14,Fsevere brain damage following his
OL,15,Fbirth at the maternity unit of
OL,16,FSingleton Hospital in Swansea in 2019.
OL,17,FHis parents, Sian and Robert Channon,
OL,18,Fhave fought for years to understand
OL,19,Fthe truth as to what happened to their
OL,20,Fson.
