OL,7,FThe Channons claimed the health board
OL,8,Fcovered up Dr Kirkup's review, while
OL,9,FDr Kirkup said the health board
OL,10,Fquestioned his credentials and ignored
OL,11,Fall further correspondence with him.
OL,12,FThe health board denied that they
OL,13,Fattempted to cover up Dr Kirkup's
OL,14,Freport.
OL,16,FNow, the health board have admitted
OL,17,Fthat failures during the resuscitation
OL,18,Fof Gethin led to his brain damage,
OL,19,Fwith the health board also apologising
OL,20,Fto the Channon family for the failures
OL,21,Fthat caused their son's injuries.
